{
  "texts": [
    "This section presents the researchers' efforts in language modelling, including Pre-Generation Retrieval Processing, Structural Model Optimization, and Post-Generation Output Enhancement.",
    "The RALM architecture initially used a single document for retrieval augmentation.",
    "However, it was discovered that RALM's performance significantly improved when the number of retrieved paragraphs was increased.",
    "(Izacard and Grave, 2020b) Therefore, they proposed a new method called Fusion-in-Decoder (FiD) which involves keeping the retriever unchanged, using the encoder in LM to encode the related documents one by one, and then connecting the related documents and giving them to the decoder for output.",
    "Then Hofstätter et al. (2023) improved on the FiD."
  ]
}